Project MythicalDash

Launch your host and benefit from our expertise in designing and coding the best pterodactyl dashboard.

Documentation

https://docs.mythicalsystems.me

Features

  • Essentials Options
  • API (Client/Admin)
  • Payment Options (Stripe)
  • Linkvertise
  • Purge System
  • Anti Alting
  • Anti VPN
  • Anti Adblocker
  • Anti Robot
  • Server Queue
  • Leaderboards
  • Support System
  • Telemetry ## Demo
You can find a live deployment copy of MythicalDash here:
  • https://devclient.mythicalsystems.me

Roadmap

You can find the roadmap at: https://github.com/orgs/MythicalLTD/projects/5

@Curiousity Is it better to use a framework or to just use no framework?
Curiousity BOT 14/05/2024 19:52
Using a framework or not depends on your project's requirements, complexity, and your familiarity with the language. Here's a breakdown: 1. Using a Framework:
  • Advantages:
    • Efficiency: Frameworks provide pre-built modules and functionalities, saving development time.
    • Consistency: Frameworks enforce coding standards, promoting consistency across the project.
    • Security: Many frameworks come with built-in security features to protect against common vulnerabilities.
  • Disadvantages:
    • Learning Curve: There might be a learning curve to understand and use the framework effectively.
    • Limitations: Frameworks may limit flexibility in some cases if the project requirements are unique.
    • Overhead: Some frameworks introduce additional overhead, affecting performance in certain scenarios.
2. Not Using a Framework:
  • Advantages:
    • Flexibility: Complete freedom to design the application structure and logic as needed.
    • Performance: Direct coding without the framework's overhead may lead to better performance in some cases.
    • Learning Experience: Offers a deeper understanding of the language and how web applications work.
  • Disadvantages:
    • Development Time: Building from scratch can be time-consuming, especially for common functionalities.
    • Maintenance: Without a framework's structure, maintaining and scaling the application may require more effort.
    • Security: Security features need to be implemented manually, potentially increasing the risk of vulnerabilities.
